<li><p>Explain how to solve <m>x^{0.4} = 18</m>, and why this method works.</p></li>
<li><p>Describe the difference between the graphs of <m>y=x^{3/4}</m> and <m>y=x^{4/3}</m>.</p></li>
<li><p>Suppose <m>M=8 \times 10^6</m>. Explain why <m>M^{2/3} = 4 \times 10^4</m>.</p></li>
</ol></p></subsection>    

